    <body>
        <p>The lower-left corner of the Termbase Editor displays information about the terms from the selected row in the grid above.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../Images/Lingo/termbase9.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent">
            </img>
        </p>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Shared/PrintOutput/EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoWhatsNewGuide,LingoGuides.LingoTermbaseGuide" />
        <p>There is a tab for each language with the term. The information in that tab is unique to that term in that language.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../Images/Lingo/termbase10.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Shared/PrintOutput/EmptyPageBreakAfter.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="LingoGuides.LingoTermbaseGuide" />
        <p>You can add a new term by clicking <img src="../../../Images/Shared/plus_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. You can remove a term by selecting it and clicking <img src="../../../Images/Shared/remove_btn.png" class="ReduceButtonSize" />. And you can add a term in a new language by clicking the plus tab.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../Images/Lingo/termbase11.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
